{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Good morning everybody."},{"time":2000,"text":"I'd like to talk about a couple of things today."},{"time":4000,"text":"The first thing is water."},{"time":6000,"text":"Now I see you've all been enjoying the water"},{"time":8000,"text":"that's been provided for you here at the conference,"},{"time":10000,"text":"over the past couple of days."},{"time":12000,"text":"And I'm sure you'll feel that it's from a safe source."}]},{"cues":[{"time":16000,"text":"But what if it wasn't?"},{"time":18000,"text":"What if it was from a source like this?"},{"time":23000,"text":"Then statistics would actually say"},{"time":25000,"text":"that half of you would now be suffering"},{"time":27000,"text":"with diarrhea."},{"time":31000,"text":"I talked a lot in the past about statistics,"},{"time":34000,"text":"and the provision of safe drinking water for all."},{"time":38000,"text":"But they just don't seem to get through."},{"time":41000,"text":"And I think I've worked out why."},{"time":43000,"text":"It's because, using current thinking,"},{"time":46000,"text":"the scale of the problem"},{"time":48000,"text":"just seems too huge to contemplate solving."},{"time":52000,"text":"So we just switch off:"},{"time":54000,"text":"us, governments and aid agencies."},{"time":59000,"text":"Well, today, I'd like to show you"},{"time":62000,"text":"that through thinking differently,"},{"time":64000,"text":"the problem has been solved."},{"time":68000,"text":"By the way, since I've been speaking,"},{"time":70000,"text":"another 13,000 people around the world"},{"time":73000,"text":"are suffering now with diarrhea."},{"time":76000,"text":"And four children have just died."}]},{"cues":[{"time":81000,"text":"I invented Lifesaver bottle"},{"time":83000,"text":"because I got angry."},{"time":85000,"text":"I, like most of you, was sitting down, the day after Christmas in 2004,"},{"time":89000,"text":"when I was watching the devastating news"},{"time":92000,"text":"of the Asian tsunami as it rolled in,"},{"time":94000,"text":"playing out on TV."},{"time":96000,"text":"The days and weeks that followed,"},{"time":98000,"text":"people fleeing to the hills,"},{"time":100000,"text":"being forced to drink contaminated water"},{"time":103000,"text":"or face death."},{"time":106000,"text":"That really stuck with me."},{"time":108000,"text":"Then, a few months later,"},{"time":111000,"text":"Hurricane Katrina slammed into the side of America."},{"time":115000,"text":"\"Okay,\" I thought, \"here's a First World country, let's see what they can do.\""},{"time":119000,"text":"Day one: nothing."},{"time":122000,"text":"Day two: nothing."},{"time":125000,"text":"Do you know it took five days to get water to the Superdome?"},{"time":130000,"text":"People were shooting each other on the streets"},{"time":133000,"text":"for TV sets and water."},{"time":136000,"text":"That's when I decided I had to do something."}]},{"cues":[{"time":140000,"text":"Now I spent a lot of time in my garage, over the next weeks and months,"},{"time":143000,"text":"and also in my kitchen -- much to the dismay of my wife. (Laughter)"},{"time":146000,"text":"However, after a few failed prototypes,"},{"time":151000,"text":"I finally came up with this, the Lifesaver bottle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":156000,"text":"Okay, now for the science bit."},{"time":158000,"text":"Before Lifesaver, the best hand filters were only capable"},{"time":160000,"text":"of filtering down to about 200 nanometers."},{"time":164000,"text":"The smallest bacteria is about 200 nanometers."},{"time":168000,"text":"So a 200-nanometer bacteria"},{"time":170000,"text":"is going to get through a 200-nanometer hole."},{"time":174000,"text":"The smallest virus, on the other hand,"},{"time":176000,"text":"is about 25 nanometers."},{"time":179000,"text":"So that's definitely going to get through those 200 nanometer holes."},{"time":184000,"text":"Lifesaver pores are 15 nanometers."},{"time":189000,"text":"So nothing is getting through."}]},{"cues":[{"time":192000,"text":"Okay, I'm going to give you a bit of a demonstration."},{"time":194000,"text":"Would you like to see that?"},{"time":196000,"text":"I spent all the time setting this up, so I guess I should."},{"time":198000,"text":"We're in the fine city of Oxford."},{"time":201000,"text":"So -- someone's done that up."},{"time":203000,"text":"Fine city of Oxford, so what I've done is I've gone"},{"time":205000,"text":"and got some water from the River Cherwell,"},{"time":207000,"text":"and the River Thames,"},{"time":209000,"text":"that flow through here. And this is the water."},{"time":211000,"text":"But I got to thinking, you know,"},{"time":213000,"text":"if we were in the middle of a flood zone"},{"time":215000,"text":"in Bangladesh, the water wouldn't look like this."},{"time":219000,"text":"So I've gone and got some stuff to add into it."},{"time":221000,"text":"And this is from my pond."}]},{"cues":[{"time":223000,"text":"(Sniffs) (Coughs) Have a smell of that, mister cameraman."}]},{"cues":[{"time":227000,"text":"Okay. (Laughs) Right."},{"time":231000,"text":"We're just going to pour that in there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":234000,"text":"Audience: Ugh!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":236000,"text":"Michael Pritchard: Okay. We've got some runoff"},{"time":239000,"text":"from a sewage plant farm."},{"time":241000,"text":"So I'm just going to put that in there."},{"time":244000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":245000,"text":"Put that in there. There we go."},{"time":248000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":249000,"text":"And some other bits and pieces, chuck that in there."},{"time":253000,"text":"And I've got a gift here from a friend of mine's rabbit."},{"time":257000,"text":"So we're just going to put that in there as well."},{"time":261000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":262000,"text":"Okay. (Laughter) Now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":266000,"text":"The Lifesaver bottle works really simply."},{"time":271000,"text":"You just scoop the water up."},{"time":273000,"text":"Today I'm going to use a jug"},{"time":275000,"text":"just to show you all. Let's get a bit of that poo in there."},{"time":279000,"text":"That's not dirty enough. Let's just stir that up a little bit."},{"time":285000,"text":"Okay, so I'm going to take this really filthy water,"},{"time":290000,"text":"and put it in here. Do you want a drink yet?"},{"time":294000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":295000,"text":"Okay. There we go."},{"time":299000,"text":"Replace the top."},{"time":304000,"text":"Give it a few pumps. Okay?"},{"time":308000,"text":"That's all that's necessary."},{"time":311000,"text":"Now as soon as I pop the teat,"},{"time":315000,"text":"sterile drinking water is going to come out."},{"time":317000,"text":"I've got to be quick. Okay, ready?"},{"time":322000,"text":"There we go. Mind the electrics."},{"time":324000,"text":"That is safe, sterile drinking water."},{"time":328000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":330000,"text":"Cheers."},{"time":332000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":335000,"text":"There you go Chris."},{"time":337000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":342000,"text":"What's it taste of?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":344000,"text":"Chris Anderson: Delicious."}]},{"cues":[{"time":346000,"text":"Michael Pritchard: Okay."},{"time":349000,"text":"Let's see Chris's program throughout the rest of the show. Okay?"},{"time":352000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":355000,"text":"Okay. Lifesaver bottle is used by thousands of people around the world."},{"time":360000,"text":"It'll last for 6,000 liters."},{"time":362000,"text":"And when it's expired, using failsafe technology,"},{"time":365000,"text":"the system will shut off, protecting the user."},{"time":368000,"text":"Pop the cartridge out. Pop a new one in."},{"time":370000,"text":"It's good for another 6,000 liters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":374000,"text":"So let's look at the applications."},{"time":376000,"text":"Traditionally, in a crisis, what do we do?"},{"time":378000,"text":"We ship water."},{"time":380000,"text":"Then, after a few weeks, we set up camps."},{"time":384000,"text":"And people are forced to come into the camps to get their safe drinking water."},{"time":389000,"text":"What happens when 20,000 people congregate in a camp?"},{"time":394000,"text":"Diseases spread. More resources are required."},{"time":397000,"text":"The problem just becomes self-perpetuating."},{"time":401000,"text":"But by thinking differently,"},{"time":403000,"text":"and shipping these,"},{"time":405000,"text":"people can stay put."},{"time":407000,"text":"They can make their own sterile drinking water,"},{"time":410000,"text":"and start to get on with rebuilding their homes and their lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":415000,"text":"Now, it doesn't require a natural disaster"},{"time":418000,"text":"for this to work."},{"time":421000,"text":"Using the old thinking, of national infrastructure"},{"time":425000,"text":"and pipe work, is too expensive."},{"time":428000,"text":"When you run the numbers on a calculator,"},{"time":430000,"text":"you run out of noughts."},{"time":432000,"text":"So here is the \"thinking different\" bit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":435000,"text":"Instead of shipping water,"},{"time":437000,"text":"and using man-made processes to do it,"},{"time":440000,"text":"let's use Mother Nature. She's got a fantastic system."},{"time":443000,"text":"She picks the water up from there,"},{"time":446000,"text":"desalinates it, for free, transports it over there,"},{"time":450000,"text":"and dumps it onto the mountains, rivers, and streams."},{"time":452000,"text":"And where do people live? Near water."},{"time":455000,"text":"All we've go to do"},{"time":457000,"text":"is make it sterile. How do we do that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":459000,"text":"Well, we could use the Lifesaver bottle."},{"time":462000,"text":"Or we could use one of these."},{"time":464000,"text":"The same technology, in a jerry can."},{"time":467000,"text":"This will process 25,000 liters of water;"},{"time":472000,"text":"that's good enough for a family of four,"},{"time":476000,"text":"for three years."},{"time":479000,"text":"And how much does it cost?"},{"time":481000,"text":"About half a cent a day to run."},{"time":483000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":485000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":488000,"text":"So, by thinking differently, and processing water"},{"time":491000,"text":"at the point of use,"},{"time":493000,"text":"mothers and children no longer have to walk four hours a day"},{"time":497000,"text":"to collect their water."},{"time":499000,"text":"They can get it from a source nearby."},{"time":503000,"text":"So with just eight billion dollars,"},{"time":506000,"text":"we can hit the millennium goal's target"},{"time":509000,"text":"of halving the number of people"},{"time":511000,"text":"without access to safe drinking water."},{"time":514000,"text":"To put that into context,"},{"time":516000,"text":"The U.K. government spends about 12 billion pounds"},{"time":520000,"text":"a year on foreign aid."},{"time":523000,"text":"But why stop there?"},{"time":526000,"text":"With 20 billion dollars, everyone can have access to safe drinking water."},{"time":532000,"text":"So the three-and-a-half billion people"},{"time":534000,"text":"that suffer every year as a result,"},{"time":537000,"text":"and the two million kids that die every year,"},{"time":541000,"text":"will live."},{"time":545000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":547000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}